# Define a reusable `Collector`

You can sum up the values of a `BigDecimal` stream using a **reusable** [`Collector`][1] named `summingUp`:

    BigDecimal sum = bigDecimalStream.collect(summingUp());

The `Collector` can be implemented like this:

    public static Collector&lt;BigDecimal, ?, BigDecimal&gt; summingUp() {
        return Collectors.reducing(BigDecimal.ZERO, BigDecimal::add);
    }


  [1]: https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/util/stream/Collector.html

If you don&#39;t mind a third party dependency, there is a class named [Collectors2][1] in [Eclipse Collections][2] which contains methods returning Collectors for [summing][3] and [summarizing][4] BigDecimal and BigInteger. These methods take a [Function][5] as a parameter so you can extract a BigDecimal or BigInteger value from an object.

